<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=frank711&Board=ranger&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Duncon (frank711) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">IMHO the main short comming of this class is the simplest one to fix.  I have never once played a RPG where rangers could not charm animals, up to now, And the one that wont let me is the best one to play.  I think this one improvement would enchance the game greatly for us.  Modifying the Enchanter charm spell (although im not a programmer, just a simple railroader) to charm any Feline/Canine animal that we could command like a pet for predetermined period of time would, for me, be a tremedous help.  I think all of us know that around the 20ish level things that con blue will kill us quick if were not careful.  Good example of this is the griffawns in N Karanas.  They are Blue at lvl 18 and im completely buffed (ranger buffs only) and the best i could do was get them to about half before root and run became necessary.  This is with Banded armor and average equipment.  The pet could be used for pulling when soloing or guarding when resting as we experience a lot of down time after a long fight.<p>

I dont know, maybe im off in left field with this..but i think it would work with proper limitions to keep the balance of order which is what class is all about.  Things like, only charming 1 at a time.<p>

share your thoughts..thats why were reading here right?<hr>Duncon Loc'Narr &lt;Bringer Clan&gt;<br>
Family First<br>
E'ci Server</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
