<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=uriel&Board=ranger&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Uriel (uriel) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:skmyers4@home.com" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to Uriel.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I have often wondered what it would be like to have animal friends.  This is a great idea for a Ranger!  What should be allowed is the following, I believe.  <p>

We should NOT be able to charm or befriend all animals, just the ones that already are amiable, such as Bears and Wolves.  Cats for the most part will attack on sight, so they should be out of the question.  <p>

But, what if we could befriend different classes of wolves and bears according to our levels.  First few levels: no animal friends.   Next few..basic wolves, brown bears.  Later levels: Grizzly Bears and the tougher Wolves.  Now that would be cool!!<p>

To be able to one day, befriend a big wolf and turn yourself into a wolf.  That's what I am talking about. <p>

Not to mention, how tough would we look with a Kodiak walking with us?<p>

Uriel Trueshot<br>
