<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I too thought that it's rather silly that a ranger can't charm a pet.  I know when I used to play D&D, most rangers would get a few pets at a determined level.  I think we should be able to grab at least 1 pet to follow us around, being that rangers are tied to nature and animals.  If you look at most rpg's, rangers have animal friends.  <br>
Good pets to rangers would be Fey Drakes, Lions, Lionesses, Bears, Wolves and the like... <br>
If you've ever read R.A. Salvatore, the most famous ranger, Drizzt Do'Urden, had Gwenhwyvar (I think that's how it's spelled), his pet panther.  I definitely think that rangers should be allowed to get pets, and not by means of a charm animal spell... A permanent pet that follows you wherever you go, and defends you if attacked, and develops a certain affinity for you.  You should be able to name it what you like too =).</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
